title: Palindrome Number
description: You are given a number. Check whether the given number is palindrome or not.
inputFormat: The first line of input contains a single integer T, denoting the number of test cases.
Each testcase consists of one line of input:
The only line of input contains a number.
outputFormat: Print 'Yes' if the given number is palindrome and 'No' otherwise.
explanation: If we reverse 11, we will get 11. Hence it is a palindrome number.
Likewise 12321 and 121 are palindrome numbers and 1231 is not.

title: Finding the Missing Number
description: Given an array containing n-1 distinct numbers within the range of 0 to n-2, find the missing number.
inputFormat: The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases.
For each test case:
The first line contains an integer n, the size of the array.
The second line contains n-1 distinct integers from the range 0 to n-1.
outputFormat: For each test case, print the missing number in a new line.
explanation: In the first sample, the input is 5, which means the array should contain numbers from 0 to 4. However, the given array only has elements 1, 2, 3, and 4. Therefore, the missing number is 0.
In the second sample, the input is 4, indicating an array with numbers from 0 to 3. The given array (0, 1, 3) is missing the number 2.

title: Maximum Subarray Sum
description: Find the contiguous subarray with the largest sum.
inputFormat: The first line contains an interger T, the number of testcases.
For each testcase:
The first line contains an integer N, the size of the array.
The second line contains N space-separated integers, representing the array elements.
outputFormat: Print the sum of the largest contiguous subarray.
explanation: The largest sum is obtained from the subarray [1 2 3], resulting in a sum of 6.
The largest sum is obtained from the subarray [2 4 6], resulting in a sum of 12.
The largest sum is obtained from the subarray [4, -1, -2, 1, 5], resulting in a sum of 7.

title: Maximum Length of Rope
description: The lengths of two ropes are m meters and n meters. Find the maximum length of a single piece of rope that can be obtained by cutting both ropes into equal-length segments.
inputFormat: The first line contains an interger T, the number of testcases.
For each testcase:
The one and only line of input consists of two space-separated integers, m and n.
outputFormat: Print the maximum length of rope in a new line.
explanation: For the lengths 8 and 4, the maximum length of rope required is 4.
For the lengths 15 and 18, the maximum length of rope required is 3.
For the lengths 126 and 275, the maximum length of rope required is 1.

title: Anagram
description: Given two strings a and b consisting of lowercase characters. The task is to check whether two given strings are an anagram of each other or not. An anagram of a string is another string that contains the same characters, only the order of characters can be different. For example, act and tac are an anagram of each other.
inputFormat: The first line contains an interger T, the number of testcases.
For each testcase:
The one and only line of input consists of two space-separated strings, a and b.
outputFormat: Print 'Yes' if the given strings are an anagram of each other, or 'No' otherwise, in a new line.
explanation: 'abc' and 'bca' have same characters with same frequency. So, both are anagrams.
Characters in 'allergy' and 'allergic' are not same, so they are not anagrams.

title: Longest Common Prefix
description: Find the longest prefix that is a common substring in all strings of a given array.
inputFormat: The first line of input contains a single integer T, the number of test cases.
Each testcase consists of two lines of input:
The first line of the testcase contains a single integer N, the size of the array.
The second line of the testcase contains N number of strings.
outputFormat: Print the longest common prefix of the given strings, in a new line.
explanation: The longest common prefix in the strings 'psychocoders' and 'psychogamer' is 'psycho'
The longest common prefix in the strings 'helloworld', 'helloprogrammer' and 'hellothere' is 'hello'
The longest common prefix in the strings 'hands', 'handsome', 'has' and 'hash' is 'ha'
